'''Literatura Latino-Americana e do Caribe em Ciências da Saúde''' (Literature in the Health Sciences in Latin America and the Caribbean, in [[Portuguese language]]), acronym '''LILACS''', is an [[on-line]] [[bibliographic database]] in [[medicine]] and [[health sciences]], maintained by the ''[[Latin American and Caribbean Center on Health Sciences Information]]'' (also known as BIREME, located in [[São Paulo]], [[Brazil]]. Similar to [[MEDLINE]], which was developed by the United States [[National Library of Medicine]], it contains bibliographic references to papers that have been published in a set of scientific and [[medical journal]]s of the region, and that are not covered by MEDLINE.

